<chapter id="Account_Statement">
  <title>Account Statement</title>

  <section condition="TITLE=Account Services: Account Statement;PERM=ab_account_statement_access"
           id="ASt" role="TOPIC">
    <title>Account Statement</title>

    <para role="TEXT">The Account Statement option provides the user with a
    statement of the accounts they are authorised to use.</para>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Account Statement - Navigation</title>

      <para role="TEXT">To navigate to the <emphasis role="bold">Account
      Statement</emphasis> function, from the tool bar, select
      <emphasis>Account Services</emphasis> &gt; <emphasis>Account
      Statement</emphasis>.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">Alternatively, if the <emphasis>Account
      Summary</emphasis>, <emphasis>Account Statement</emphasis> or
      <emphasis>Account Details</emphasis> functions have already been
      selected, there will be a link to the <emphasis role="bold">Account
      Statement</emphasis> function in the left hand side navigation
      list.</para>
    </section>
    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Account Statement Selection</title>

      <para role="TEXT">When the <emphasis role="bold">Account
      Statement</emphasis> function is selected, the system will display a
      list of criteria that must be selected to identify the account and
      period of the statement.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">The list is not displayed until search criteria has
      been entered and the <emphasis role="bold">Search</emphasis> button has
      been clicked. The fields required are as follows:</para>

      <para role="TEXT"><informaltable role="TEXT">
          <tgroup cols="3">
            <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

            <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1.0*"/>

            <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="6.0*"/>

            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Field</para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Type</para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Description</para></entry>
              </row>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><guilabel moreinfo="none">
                Company</guilabel></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_info.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_INFO" width="4mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top">The company the user belongs to.</entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><guilabel moreinfo="none">
                Entity</guilabel></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_action.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_ACTION" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top">Enter the Entity the account belongs to.
                Click the magnifying glass icon to display and select from a
                list of valid Entities.</entry>
              </row>
              
			<row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Bank</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                      <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/char_arrow.gif"
                                   role="CHAR_ARROW" width="2mm" />
                      </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The bank holding the
                requested account.</para><note>
                    <para role="TEXT">If you are linked to more than one bank, 
                    the Bank dropdown is available. If you are linked to 
                    only one bank, this field doesnâ€™t appear.</para>
                  </note>
                </entry>
              </row>


              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><guilabel moreinfo="none"> Account
                Number</guilabel></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_action.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_ACTION" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top">Enter the account number of the required
                statement. Click the magnifying glass icon to display and
                select from a list of valid accounts.</entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Date
                Range</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_radio.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_RADIO" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Select the period the statement
                should report on. Valid periods are: <programlisting
                format="linespecific">Current Day
Previous Day
Current Month
Previous Month
From: to: - enter the from and to statement dates.</programlisting></para></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </informaltable></para>
 
      <para role="TEXT">There is also a download button that allows the
      results to be saved as a file on the executing PC. Click this button and
      select the required option from the list shown. The options are:</para>

      <itemizedlist role="TEXT">
        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT"><type>CSV</type> downloads the list to the PC as
          Comma-Separated Values file.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT"><type>Spreadsheet</type> downloads the list to the PC as a
          <productname class="trade">Microsoft Excel</productname> compatible
          file.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT"><type>MT940</type> downloads the list to the PC as a SWIFT
          compatible file.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
      <para role="TEXT">Use the <guilabel>CSV</guilabel>,
      <guilabel>SpreadSheet</guilabel> or <guilabel>MT940</guilabel> option to
      export the list as a report allowing it to be customised further for
      various office productivity tools. When the browser displays the
      <literal moreinfo="none">File Download</literal> prompt, save the file
      or directly open it to launch in the default viewer if available on the
      workstation.</para>
      <para role="TEXT">When all fields have been completed, click the
      <emphasis role="bold">SEARCH</emphasis> button to produce the statement.
      The statement produced will show the following columns:</para>

      <para role="TEXT"><informaltable role="TEXT">
          <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

            <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*"/>

            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Field</para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Description</para></entry>
              </row>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Transaction Date</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The date the transaction took place.
                </para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Value
                Date</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The time the transaction took
                place.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Description</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The description of the
                transaction.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Deposit</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The amount that was
                deposited.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Withdrawal</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The amount that was
                withdrawn.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Balance</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The balance in the account, after
                the transaction.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"></para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">MT940</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The above details are for the PDF
                and CSV downloads. However, for MT940, the details are in the
                SWIFT format and are given in the rows below.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel moreinfo="none">SWIFT
                MT940 File Rows</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The rows in the SWIFT format are
                represented by codes. The codes and the corresponding
                decriptions are given below.</para><note>
                    <para role="TEXT">The rows with details will be available in the
                    downloaded statement. Rows where details have not been
                    entered will not appear in the statement. </para>
                  </note><para role="TEXT"><programlisting format="linespecific">20 - Transaction Reference Number (Mandatory)
21 - Related Reference (Optional)
25 - Account Identification (Mandatory)
28C - Statement Number/Sequence Number (Mandatory)
60a - Opening Balance (Mandatory)
61 - Statement Line (Optional)
86 - Information to Account Owner (Optional)
62a - Closing Balance (Booked Funds) (Mandatory)
64 - Closing Available Balance (Optional)
65 - Forward Available Balance (Optional)
86 - Information to Account Owner (Optional)</programlisting></para></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </informaltable></para>

      <note>
        <para role="TEXT">All amounts are displayed in the account
        currency.</para>
      </note>
        
      <para role="TEXT">There is also a download button that allows the
      results to be saved as a file on the executing PC. Click this button and
      select the required option from the list shown. The options are:</para>

      <itemizedlist role="TEXT">
        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT"><type>CSV</type> downloads the list to the PC as
          Comma-Separated Values file.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT"><type>Spreadsheet</type> downloads the list to the PC as a
          <productname class="trade">Microsoft Excel</productname> compatible
          file.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT"><type>MT940</type> downloads the list to the PC as a SWIFT
          compatible file.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

      <para role="TEXT">Use the <guilabel>CSV</guilabel>,
      <guilabel>SpreadSheet</guilabel> or <guilabel>MT940</guilabel> option to
      export the list as a report allowing it to be customised further for
      various office productivity tools. When the browser displays the
      <literal moreinfo="none">File Download</literal> prompt, save the file
      or directly open it to launch in the default viewer if available on the
      workstation.</para>
      
      <para>The user will be able to see displayed </para>

